## Overview

This plugin provides the `{{.Name}}.handler` module type to the workflow engine.

## Build

```bash
go build -o {{.Name}}.plugin .
```

## Usage

Reference this plugin from your workflow config:

```yaml
requires:
  plugins:
    - name: {{.Name}}
      path: ./{{.Name}}.plugin

modules:
  - name: my-handler
    type: {{.Name}}.handler
    config:
      timeout: 30s
```

## Development

### Adding Module Types

Add a new factory in `ModuleFactories()` in `plugin.go`:

```go
"{{.Name}}.my-type": func(name string, cfg map[string]any) modular.Module {
    return NewMyModule(name, cfg)
},
```

### Adding Pipeline Steps

Add a new factory in `StepFactories()` in `plugin.go`:

```go
"step.{{.Name}}.my-step": func(name string, cfg map[string]any, app modular.Application) (any, error) {
    return NewMyStep(name, cfg, app), nil
},
```

